<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-24T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-24T06:00:00-05:00" n="1274" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1274">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/4–2449: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-24T19:00:00+08:00">April 24,
                                    1949—7 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received April 24—7:41 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1327. Admiral Badger in conversation this afternoon said that he was
                            studying possibility of modified emergency evacuation plan which would
                            provide protection for civilians essentially as contemplated (mytel
                            1319).</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>